      • db_is_null_p

        public abstract boolean db_is_null_p(int column_index)
                              throws exc_database_error
        Returns true iff the value in the specified column of the current row is null (meaning SQL NULL or an equivalent). Note that some odd data sources treat the empty string as null, or null as the empty string (for example: the Excel driver).
        Throws:
        exc_database_error
